.TH "map_skb" 9 "map_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
map_skb \- map an skb for DMA to the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" map_skb
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the egress net device
.IP "skb" 12
the packet to map
.IP "addr" 12
a pointer to the base of the DMA mapping array

Map an skb for DMA to the device and return an array of DMA addresses.
